Thinking Fella Feb 11 · 03:25:54 PM
Thanks for this report, and even more—thanks for being a proud Dem in a red State! If you happen to know any of the folks who showed up, please tell them some guy in rural Colorado is applauding them admiringly & hopes they keep up the fight.

We are also quite active here in our little town, mostly via Indivisible right now, hounding our R Congressional Rep & 1 of our Senators who is R. And just like you, when 50 or 100 folks show up for anything in a small town, it’s news, so it gets covered. Enough signs & you get a pic in the paper! Rural representatives have to respond to that stuff, whereas in a big city, 100 folks is just how many are waiting for the traffic light to change at an intersection & city folk need many 1000’s to be noticed. I’m a believer that out here in rural areas, across the country, if every town has a protest at every opportunity, it will have an impact. Most new votes to be found—in the places we need for Congress, Senate & electoral college for president not to mention local races, exist out here in the sticks. I learned today that my county had an 84% turnout last election (and it was a blue wave in my county, but we couldn’t carry our Congress dist), and that was because my county rallied every available Dem to do something in addition to voting. I have every expectation I will be calling my precinct many times well before the next election, and I expect they will respond again. 

Thanks again for your active participation in our democracy!

